704328f-a.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Avenue U
704328f-a.text:
Flatbush Ave., at the N.E. corner of Ave. U, showing the end of the Flat-
bush trolley line. This section is as yet undeveloped.
February 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
704328f-a.folder: Flatbush Avenue & Avenue U, Brooklyn, NY

704330f-d.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Avenue U
704330f-d.text:
(1)
Flatbush Ave., (right) south of Ave. U to Rockaway Inlet, showing a
pier at the foot of Flatbush Ave. under construction. Mill Basin is at
the left.
May 12, 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, from another angle. The first pier on Jamaica Bay was opened
for business on June 1, 1898.
August 1925.
Eugene E. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, another angle, showing Mill Basin and Mill Island on the
Meft.
August 1925.
Eugene L.Ammbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(4)
The same, viewed north, showing Mill Basin. Flatbush Ave. is in the
background with raised wires thereon.
August 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
704330f-d.folder: Flatbush Avenue & Avenue U, Brooklyn, NY

704329f-a.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Avenue U
704329f-a.text:
Flatbush Ave., at the S.E. corner of Ave. U. This place has long been
abandoned.
February 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
